<TITLE> 2 Chittagong jail prisoners die </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 4(bdnews24.com)  Two prisoners of Chittagong jail died of illness on Thursday, a jail official said. The deceased are Ilyas, 32, and Rohindra Tripura, 42. "Ilyas and Rohindra died in Chittagong Medical College Hospital respectively in the morning and afternoon," said senior superintendent of Chittagong jail Ataur Rahman to bdnews24.com. "Ilyas, who had been jailed for 15 years in two cases, had been undergoing treatment in the hospital for four months for cancer." He also said, "Rohindra, a defendant in a murder case, had been taking treatment for two months in the jail hospital. As he fell seriously ill, he was rushed to CMCH at around 4pm and after a while, he died there." "The bodies were handed over to their relatives after formalities," he added. bd
